<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2015-10-28</DATELINE><TITLE>High Prevalence of Mycoplasma faucium DNA in the Human Oropharynx</TITLE><BODY>Mycoplasma faucium has recently been associated with brain abscesses and seems to originate from the mouth. We evaluated its prevalence by quantitative real-time PCR (qPCR) in the oropharynxes of 644 subjects and found that 25% harbored M. faucium, probably constituting the gateway for entrance of the bacteria into cerebral abscesses.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>